limanis, A.S., Kunin, W.E., Lennon, J.J., Sgardelis, S.P., Uses and abuses of fractal methodology in ecology (2004) Ecol. Lett., 7, pp. 254-271; Holdsworth, A.R., Uhl, C., Fire in Amazonian selectively logged rain forest and the potential for fire reduction (1997) Ecol. Appl., 7, pp. 713-725; Jaynes, E.T., Prior probabilities (1968) IEEE Trans. Sys. Sci. Cyb., SSC, 4, pp. 227-241; Jensen, H.J., (1998) Self-Organized Criticality, , Cambridge University Press, Cambridge; Jones, C., Lowe, J., Liddicoat, S., Betts, R., Committed terrestrial ecosystem changes due to climate change (2009) Nat. Geosci., 2, pp. 484-487; Keitt, T.H., Marquet, P.A., The introduced Hawaiian avifauna reconsidered: evidence for self-organized criticality? (1996) J. Theor. Biol., 182, pp. 161-167; Keitt, T.H., Stanley, H.E., Dynamics of North American breeding bird populations (1998) Nature, 393, pp. 257-260; Levin, S.A., Self-organization and the emergence of complexity in ecological systems (2005) Bioscience, 55, pp. 1075-1079; MacKay, G., Jan, N., Forest fires as critical phenomena (1984) J. Phys. A: Math. Gen., 17, pp. L757-L760; Malamud, B.D., Morein, G., Turcotte, D.L., Forest fires: an example of self-organized critical behavior (1998) Science, 281, pp. 1840-1842; Malamud, B.D., Millington, J.D.A., Perry, G.L.W., Characterizing wildfire regimes in the United States (2005) Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA, 102, pp. 4694-4699; Malhi, Y., Aragão, L.E.O.C., Galbraith, D., Huntingford, C., Fisher, R., Zelazowski, P., Exploring the likelihood and mechanism of a climate-change-induced dieback of the Amazon rainforest (2009) Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA, 106, pp. 20610-20615; Nelson, B.W., Fogo em florestas da Amazônia Central em 1997 (2007) Anais X Simpósio Brasileiro de Sensoriamento Remoto, pp. 1675-1782. , INPE, Foz do Iguaçú, Brazil; Nepstad, D.C., Veríssimo, A., Alencar, A., Nobre, C., Lima, E., Lefebvre, P., Large-scale impoverishment of Amazonian forests by logging and fire (1999) Nature, 398, pp.